WEBVTT

00:04.221 --> 00:04.439
.

00:04.482 --> 00:06.180
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:06.223 --> 00:07.485
sexually based offenses

00:07.529 --> 00:09.792
are considered
especially heinous.

00:09.835 --> 00:12.360
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:12.403 --> 00:14.144
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:14.188 --> 00:15.624
are members of an elite squad

00:15.667 --> 00:17.408
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:17.452 --> 00:19.236
These are their stories.

00:22.109 --> 00:24.546
- Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

00:24.589 --> 00:29.377
It's been four weeks
since my last confession.

00:32.380 --> 00:36.688
I've committed
the sin of adultery...

00:36.732 --> 00:39.474
twice.

00:39.517 --> 00:42.390
And I'm afraid
I'm gonna do it again.

00:42.433 --> 00:46.524
My husband is working late
next Friday.

00:46.568 --> 00:48.657
The last time
my lover came over,

00:48.700 --> 00:52.095
I left the door unlocked.

00:52.139 --> 00:55.098
And he wants me to do it again.

00:55.142 --> 00:57.100
- Open the door to Jesus,
my child,

00:57.144 --> 00:59.189
but lock the door to sin.

00:59.233 --> 01:01.365
- I always say I will.

01:01.409 --> 01:05.152
I know it's wrong.

01:05.195 --> 01:08.851
But I get weak, Father.

01:09.591 --> 01:14.552
- I'm Burton,
and I'm an alcoholic.

01:14.596 --> 01:15.988
I've been sober
for five months,

01:16.032 --> 01:20.167
two weeks, and three days,
but who's counting?

01:20.210 --> 01:25.389
And in that time,
my life has changed... a lot.

01:25.433 --> 01:28.131
But like others here,

01:28.175 --> 01:33.136
before I found these rooms,
there was no bottom for me.

01:33.180 --> 01:36.096
[quiet dramatic music]

01:36.139 --> 01:38.315
♪

01:38.359 --> 01:40.012
- Think a lot
of people identified

01:40.056 --> 01:42.667
with what you shared.
- Mm.

01:42.711 --> 01:45.409
- So now tell me
how it's really going.

01:45.453 --> 01:47.411
- Well, I've had
my ups and downs.

01:47.455 --> 01:50.936
But I haven't picked up.
I'm working my program.

01:50.980 --> 01:52.503
- Finish your eighth step?

01:52.547 --> 01:53.678
- I have.

01:53.722 --> 01:57.465
The list of people I've harmed
is long.

01:57.508 --> 01:59.554
- And now the ninth step.

01:59.597 --> 02:03.123
- How do you even begin to make
amends to all these people?

02:03.166 --> 02:05.951
- You're a novelist.

02:05.995 --> 02:08.780
Pick a place to start.

02:08.824 --> 02:13.133
Maybe the beginning?

02:13.176 --> 02:15.178
- Come back
to Staten Island with me.

02:15.222 --> 02:18.268
I can cook.
You could spend the night.

02:18.312 --> 02:19.530
- [sighs]
Can you wait here?

02:19.574 --> 02:21.228
I need to go to confession.

02:21.271 --> 02:23.795
- Again?
Didn't you just go last week?

02:23.839 --> 02:27.451
Are you okay, Audrey?

02:28.235 --> 02:29.627
[sighs]

02:29.671 --> 02:31.238
- Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

02:32.717 --> 02:35.503
I failed God.

02:35.546 --> 02:38.201
As much as I tried to resist,

02:38.245 --> 02:42.292
I still planned
to commit adultery.

02:42.336 --> 02:46.818
But I paid the price
for betrayal.

02:46.862 --> 02:51.780
I was raped last night.

02:51.823 --> 02:54.174
God's truly angry.

02:54.217 --> 02:56.654
[quiet dramatic music]

02:56.698 --> 03:00.005
♪

03:00.049 --> 03:01.920
- Hey, Caitlin.

03:01.964 --> 03:03.226
- Sonny!
[chuckles]

03:03.270 --> 03:04.923
- How you doing?
- Hi, I'm good.

03:04.967 --> 03:06.490
- What are you doing
off of Staten Island?

03:06.534 --> 03:08.231
At a church, no less.
What, did you finally un-lapse?

03:08.275 --> 03:09.537
- [scoffs]
Bite your tongue.

03:09.580 --> 03:10.842
I--I'm waiting for Audrey.

03:10.886 --> 03:12.192
- Yeah, sure, Audrey,
your little sister.

03:12.235 --> 03:13.628
I see her at mass all the time.
We say hello.

03:13.671 --> 03:15.325
- Yeah.
What are you doing here?

03:15.369 --> 03:16.761
You need to spill
your sins too?

03:16.805 --> 03:17.980
- Ah, no, I'm actually--

03:18.023 --> 03:19.547
I'm just--I'm saying hello
to Father Duffy.

03:19.590 --> 03:21.288
- Look at you, Sonny.

03:21.331 --> 03:23.290
A detective
and then law school--

03:23.333 --> 03:24.856
I heard you're an ADA now.

03:24.900 --> 03:28.208
- I guess I'm a late bloomer.
- [chuckles]

03:28.251 --> 03:32.690
I should go.
Um...

03:32.734 --> 03:34.779
Audrey's going
through... a time.

03:34.823 --> 03:37.565
It was good to see you, Sonny.
- Yeah, you too.

03:41.351 --> 03:43.484
- Dominick,
sorry to keep you waiting.

03:43.527 --> 03:46.313
- Hey, Ryan.
Sorry, Father Duffy.

03:46.356 --> 03:47.488
How you doing?
Thanks for meeting me.

03:47.531 --> 03:48.706
Hey, Father Regis,
how are you?

03:48.750 --> 03:50.621
- Very exciting news,
I hear, Dominick?

03:50.665 --> 03:52.101
Aren't you here
for a Pre-Cana?

03:52.144 --> 03:53.233
- [sighs]
- You set a date yet?

03:53.276 --> 03:54.712
- Well, she hasn't
even said yes.

03:54.756 --> 03:56.148
In fact,
I haven't even asked her yet,

03:56.192 --> 03:57.672
so it's still early stages.

03:57.715 --> 03:59.064
- You need me
to put in a word upstairs?

03:59.108 --> 04:00.283
- Oh, I'm sure he's got
enough on his plate,

04:00.327 --> 04:03.591
but thank you.
- Okay. Ryan.

04:03.634 --> 04:05.462
- Let's go to the rectory.

04:05.506 --> 04:07.638
- Hey, can I--
can I ask you something?

04:07.682 --> 04:09.988
Audrey O'Neill--
she seemed--she seemed upset.

04:10.032 --> 04:11.381
- You know
I can't really speak to that.

04:11.425 --> 04:12.774
- Why, 'cause you took
her confession?

04:12.817 --> 04:14.297
I'm sorry,
I know I can't ask that either.

04:14.341 --> 04:17.909
- No.
But... she's a friend?

04:17.953 --> 04:20.782
Never hurts to reach out.

04:23.611 --> 04:25.395
- I'm just asking you
to listen.

04:25.439 --> 04:27.049
I'm not asking you
to forgive me.

04:27.092 --> 04:31.009
- Okay.
I'm listening.

04:31.053 --> 04:32.402
- I'm aware
that the last time we met,

04:32.446 --> 04:35.100
I wasn't at my best.

04:35.144 --> 04:38.626
- You threw a glass at me.
- Uh-uh, at the door.

04:39.975 --> 04:44.936
Well, turns out, that night,
I hit bottom.

04:49.027 --> 04:50.638
You said you wanted
acknowledgement

04:50.681 --> 04:53.249
that what happened between us
when you were 16 was wrong.

04:53.293 --> 04:54.642
And I think I said--

04:54.685 --> 04:57.775
- You said, "Well, you're
not gonna get it."

04:57.819 --> 05:00.735
- Did I?
Okay, that sounds right.

05:00.778 --> 05:03.041
I was drinking a lot.
I don't remember

05:03.085 --> 05:07.611
exactly what--
- I do.

05:07.655 --> 05:09.439
- You're still angry.

05:09.483 --> 05:12.442
- Yeah, I'm angry.

05:12.486 --> 05:14.226
- Would it help
if you threw a glass at me?

05:14.270 --> 05:16.272
- No, Burton, it wouldn't.

05:16.316 --> 05:18.492
- I'm sorry.
I'm--I'm--I'm--

05:18.535 --> 05:19.928
Olivia, I'm trying
to make amends.

05:19.971 --> 05:23.279
- You're sorry?
You're sorry for what?

05:23.323 --> 05:25.847
You're sorry for abusing women?

05:25.890 --> 05:27.022
For using women?

05:27.065 --> 05:29.981
For hiding behind alcohol
as an excuse?

05:31.983 --> 05:34.246
Look, I just want to make sure
that you understand

05:34.290 --> 05:37.206
what making amends means.

05:37.249 --> 05:40.078
And not just to me, Burton,

05:40.122 --> 05:42.037
but to the other women.

05:42.080 --> 05:44.996
[somber music]

05:45.040 --> 05:46.128
♪

05:46.171 --> 05:48.435
To acknowledge
what you did to them.

05:48.478 --> 05:50.393
- That's exactly why I'm here.

05:50.437 --> 05:53.265
I hear you.
And I'm trying.

05:53.309 --> 05:56.660
- Well, good.
Good.

05:58.445 --> 06:00.229
So let me know
when you've done that.

06:00.272 --> 06:07.454
♪

06:07.497 --> 06:10.413
[dramatic music]

06:10.457 --> 06:17.594
♪

06:54.501 --> 06:54.675
.

06:54.718 --> 06:56.111
- Thank you for meeting me.

06:56.154 --> 06:57.286
- I'm glad you called.

06:57.329 --> 06:58.940
You're worried about Audrey.
I am too.

06:58.983 --> 07:00.985
- I mean, look, it's--
it's none of my business,

07:01.029 --> 07:03.379
but I just seen that look
of trauma before, and...

07:03.423 --> 07:04.946
Did--did she tell you anything?

07:04.989 --> 07:07.775
- Not much.

07:07.818 --> 07:11.431
She did confide in me
that she's having an affair.

07:11.474 --> 07:13.607
I think maybe her husband,
Shane, found out.

07:13.650 --> 07:14.956
- And he knocked her around?

07:14.999 --> 07:17.567
I've seen him at mass.
He's an intimidating guy.

07:17.611 --> 07:18.742
- He's a guard at Rikers.

07:18.786 --> 07:19.917
Moonlights
as a nightclub bouncer.

07:19.961 --> 07:21.310
Drinks a lot.

07:21.353 --> 07:23.312
I--I told her
to come and stay with me,

07:23.355 --> 07:24.574
but she refused.

07:24.618 --> 07:27.490
Swears Shane didn't hurt her.

07:27.534 --> 07:29.144
I worry she's
just protecting him.

07:29.187 --> 07:31.538
- Well, maybe you could get her
to--to talk to me

07:31.581 --> 07:33.888
or my old boss at SVU,
Olivia Benson?

07:33.931 --> 07:35.324
Nothing formal.
It's just sometimes it's

07:35.367 --> 07:37.935
easier to share with people
outside of the family.

07:37.979 --> 07:41.852
- I think another woman
would be a good idea.

07:41.896 --> 07:44.551
- Burton Lowe, that creep?
What's he want?

07:44.594 --> 07:46.553
- He says that he wants
to make amends.

07:46.596 --> 07:47.945
- What's he really want?

07:47.989 --> 07:51.122
- I think he really wants
to make amends.

07:51.166 --> 07:53.037
- Well, it's not up to you
to let him off the hook.

07:53.081 --> 07:55.518
- I told him that, Fin.

07:55.562 --> 07:57.825
But, I don't know--I--

07:57.868 --> 08:00.175
I was up all night,
thinking about him.

08:00.218 --> 08:02.003
- Thinking about who?
- Guess who's back?

08:02.046 --> 08:03.831
Burton Lowe.
- What did he do now?

08:03.874 --> 08:05.789
- He asked
for Liv's forgiveness.

08:05.833 --> 08:07.661
- Why, so he can write
another book about it?

08:07.704 --> 08:10.054
- I think we can assume
that he hit bottom.

08:10.098 --> 08:11.795
So if he is trying
to turn his life around,

08:11.839 --> 08:14.232
isn't the right thing to do

08:14.276 --> 08:15.538
to hear him out?
- Yeah, probably.

08:15.582 --> 08:16.887
I mean, I never liked that guy
from the get,

08:16.931 --> 08:19.324
but let he
who is without sin...

08:19.368 --> 08:22.806
Uh, speaking of which,
I, uh--I have an old friend.

08:22.850 --> 08:24.155
Her sister might be
in some trouble.

08:24.199 --> 08:26.854
I don't know
if it's DV or something else.

08:26.897 --> 08:30.553
- You think she needs
to talk to someone?

08:30.597 --> 08:33.382
- I didn't really want
the police involved.

08:33.425 --> 08:35.297
My husband can't know
any of this.

08:35.340 --> 08:37.125
- Where is your husband now?

08:37.168 --> 08:38.822
- Shane's working a double
at Rikers.

08:38.866 --> 08:40.694
- Hey, whatever happened
to you, Audrey,

08:40.737 --> 08:42.652
we're just--
we're just here to listen.

08:42.696 --> 08:43.740
Okay?
You don't have to worry

08:43.784 --> 08:46.874
about filing a police report.

08:46.917 --> 08:48.745
- Okay.

08:48.789 --> 08:54.185
Well, what happened is,
I was raped.

08:54.229 --> 08:56.492
I--I have no idea by who.

08:56.536 --> 08:58.712
- Okay, um...

08:58.755 --> 09:00.322
is there anything
that you can tell us,

09:00.365 --> 09:04.587
like when it happened
or where?

09:04.631 --> 09:06.589
- Friday night, my apartment.

09:06.633 --> 09:09.897
Shane was working late.

09:09.940 --> 09:13.422
I know that Caitlin told Sonny
my marriage is in cold storage.

09:13.465 --> 09:16.120
I've been having a fling

09:16.164 --> 09:17.513
with my upstairs neighbor...

09:17.557 --> 09:20.734
- Okay.
- For about a month.

09:20.777 --> 09:22.083
I'm no perfect Catholic.

09:22.126 --> 09:23.911
- Hey, none of us are.
- Look, we're not--

09:23.954 --> 09:26.827
we're not here to judge you.
Okay?

09:26.870 --> 09:31.658
So, um, do you have any idea
how he got into your apartment?

09:31.701 --> 09:34.661
- I left the door unlocked
for my neighbor.

09:34.704 --> 09:36.271
Vince was supposed
to come over at 10:00,

09:36.314 --> 09:39.622
but right before that,
some stranger comes in

09:39.666 --> 09:42.277
with a ski mask and gloves.

09:42.320 --> 09:43.757
Before I could scream,

09:43.800 --> 09:49.676
he started choking me
with a--a belt, I think.

09:49.719 --> 09:54.506
He, uh, forced himself
inside me.

09:54.550 --> 09:58.075
It was quick,
and then he just left.

09:58.119 --> 10:01.513
- And you're sure it wasn't
this--this guy, Vince?

10:01.557 --> 10:04.342
- I don't think so.
I--

10:04.386 --> 10:06.693
He felt different.

10:06.736 --> 10:09.913
Vince is well-endowed.

10:09.957 --> 10:11.785
- Okay.

10:11.828 --> 10:13.700
Okay, did anybody else know

10:13.743 --> 10:15.484
that you were gonna leave
the door unlocked?

10:15.527 --> 10:18.792
- No.
But... Vince came in

10:18.835 --> 10:20.054
right after
the guy who raped me left

10:20.097 --> 10:22.796
and found me.
He was pretty upset.

10:22.839 --> 10:27.322
- How well do you know Vince?

10:27.365 --> 10:29.019
- Not that well.

10:29.063 --> 10:31.979
Separated from his wife,
I think.

10:32.022 --> 10:35.896
Moved in a couple months ago.

10:35.939 --> 10:38.202
[scoffs]

10:38.246 --> 10:42.337
I guess I don't really know him
at all.

10:42.380 --> 10:45.340
[dramatic music]

10:45.383 --> 10:48.735
♪

10:48.778 --> 10:50.650
- Vince Costa, 42.

10:50.693 --> 10:52.869
Declared bankruptcy
after a messy divorce.

10:52.913 --> 10:54.436
He works at a car dealership.

10:54.479 --> 10:56.525
- He got a record?
- Minor stuff.

10:56.568 --> 10:58.701
Bookmaking, credit card fraud.

10:58.745 --> 11:00.921
- Might be a wise guy
trying to pay off a debt,

11:00.964 --> 11:03.532
offering up Audrey
as some kind of payment.

11:03.575 --> 11:06.230
Vince Costa!

11:06.274 --> 11:07.841
Detective Velasco,

11:07.884 --> 11:10.191
Sergeant Tutuola,
Special Victims.

11:10.234 --> 11:11.671
- This about Audrey?

11:11.714 --> 11:12.846
- Yeah, what do you know
about that?

11:12.889 --> 11:13.934
- Listen, I was the one
who found her.

11:13.977 --> 11:15.239
All right?
She was hysterical.

11:15.283 --> 11:16.632
I--I told her to call 911.

11:16.676 --> 11:19.287
I mean, she must
have told you that, right?

11:19.330 --> 11:21.115
Do you have any idea
who--who it was? Or--

11:21.158 --> 11:22.943
- We're hoping
you could help us.

11:22.986 --> 11:24.988
Somebody knew
the door was gonna be unlocked.

11:25.032 --> 11:26.381
You tell one of your pals
about your fling?

11:26.424 --> 11:28.383
- Listen, man,
I'm going through a divorce.

11:28.426 --> 11:30.211
My wife doesn't let me
bring the kids here.

11:30.254 --> 11:32.213
There's no way I'm telling
anybody about an affair, no.

11:32.256 --> 11:35.085
- Any chance somebody overheard
you and Audrey talking?

11:35.129 --> 11:36.739
- No way.

11:36.783 --> 11:38.567
I mean, I don't know,
maybe her uh, husband's

11:38.610 --> 11:39.742
tapping her phone?

11:39.786 --> 11:41.831
I mean, have--
have you talked to him?

11:41.875 --> 11:42.876
You know?
He's built like a--

11:42.919 --> 11:44.225
he's built like a war memorial.

11:44.268 --> 11:46.183
And Audrey says he has friends
that are ex-cons.

11:46.227 --> 11:48.838
Could have sent one of them
over to attack her.

11:48.882 --> 11:50.187
That dude is scary.

11:50.231 --> 11:52.886
- And you were sleeping
with his wife?

11:52.929 --> 11:55.323
- Wasn't supposed
to find out, you know.

11:55.366 --> 11:56.672
- Well, he will now.

11:56.716 --> 11:58.935
Might want to watch your back.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.288
- Burton, hi.

12:04.332 --> 12:06.029
I'm in the middle
of a very busy day.

12:06.073 --> 12:08.118
And I--I--I can't
talk to you right now.

12:08.162 --> 12:09.772
- I was just at a meeting
in the neighborhood,

12:09.816 --> 12:13.036
and had a thought.

12:13.080 --> 12:16.039
I'm qualifying tomorrow
at my home group.

12:16.083 --> 12:19.260
And, um, maybe you'd want
to come?

12:19.303 --> 12:22.306
It wouldn't be about us.

12:22.350 --> 12:24.874
Maybe that's loaded for you.
Anyway.

12:24.918 --> 12:27.268
- Yeah.
Um, I'll think about it.

12:27.311 --> 12:28.791
- All right, all right.
Well, thanks anyway.

12:28.835 --> 12:30.750
- Yeah, sure.

12:32.926 --> 12:36.103
No, Fin, don't--don't ask.

12:36.146 --> 12:37.887
Where are we on Audrey's case?

12:37.931 --> 12:39.889
The neighbor boyfriend's
a bottom-feeder,

12:39.933 --> 12:41.325
but I don't think it's him.

12:41.369 --> 12:43.240
- Well, I think
it's highly unlikely

12:43.284 --> 12:44.676
that someone was checking
doorknobs.

12:44.720 --> 12:46.069
I mean, the timing--

12:46.113 --> 12:48.202
Look, this guy was
clearly tipped off

12:48.245 --> 12:49.551
about the open door.

12:49.594 --> 12:51.292
- No security cameras,
nothing on the canvass.

12:51.335 --> 12:52.641
But Audrey has agreed

12:52.684 --> 12:54.643
to let CSU search
the apartment.

12:54.686 --> 12:55.949
- So the husband knows?

12:55.992 --> 12:57.298
- Not about the affair.

12:57.341 --> 12:58.908
But she said she'd tell him
about the assault.

12:58.952 --> 13:00.040
- There's no chance

13:00.083 --> 13:01.432
that the husband was
the rapist?

13:01.476 --> 13:02.956
- Club security footage
puts him at work,

13:02.999 --> 13:04.609
but he could have sent

13:04.653 --> 13:06.089
one of the goons
that works for him.

13:06.133 --> 13:08.004
- Well, if he did hire
one of his ex-cons,

13:08.048 --> 13:09.223
then they'd be in the system.

13:09.266 --> 13:11.355
So maybe we get lucky
with the DNA.

13:16.230 --> 13:17.927
- How much longer
is this gonna take?

13:17.971 --> 13:19.146
Fingerprints, I get.

13:19.189 --> 13:20.756
But they're looking
for hidden cameras?

13:20.800 --> 13:22.192
- We're trying to figure out
how someone knew

13:22.236 --> 13:23.672
about your affair.

13:23.715 --> 13:24.891
- Can you tell them to hurry?

13:24.934 --> 13:27.328
- This is my apartment.
Let me in.

13:27.371 --> 13:29.852
The hell's going on?
- Shane, you're home early.

13:29.896 --> 13:31.898
- I thought you said
you told him.

13:31.941 --> 13:34.074
- Told me what?
- Let's stay calm, Mr. O'Neill.

13:34.117 --> 13:35.466
- Who the hell are you, pal?

13:35.510 --> 13:36.816
- Manhattan ADA Carisi.

13:36.859 --> 13:37.729
Your wife has given us
permission

13:37.773 --> 13:39.557
to search this apartment.

13:39.601 --> 13:41.472
She's a crime victim.
- What?

13:41.516 --> 13:43.561
- I didn't want to upset you.

13:43.605 --> 13:45.259
But I was raped.

13:46.738 --> 13:47.739
- You mean you knew

13:47.783 --> 13:48.915
I was working a double shift

13:48.958 --> 13:52.005
and you had some guy over here.

13:52.048 --> 13:54.007
He sent you flowers
the next day?

13:54.050 --> 13:56.009
- Those are from the parish.
- You're lying.

13:56.052 --> 13:58.881
You are lying.
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

13:58.925 --> 14:01.449
Listen, we're all
brother officers here.

14:01.492 --> 14:03.973
- Listen, man, your wife
was sexually assaulted.

14:04.017 --> 14:05.540
She didn't tell you

14:05.583 --> 14:07.890
'cause she was afraid
you'd react like this.

14:07.934 --> 14:12.503
Why don't you prove her wrong?

14:12.547 --> 14:14.984
- He thinks I'm lying.

14:15.028 --> 14:18.379
I swore before God
about everything.

14:18.422 --> 14:22.035
You mean in confession?
- Yeah.

14:22.078 --> 14:25.081
I asked for the strength
to stop cheating on my husband.

14:25.125 --> 14:28.868
- So aside from your sister
and Vince,

14:28.911 --> 14:32.959
a priest also knew
about your affair?

14:33.002 --> 14:35.918
- Yeah, he absolved me.

14:35.962 --> 14:38.965
- Audrey, did you tell
the priest

14:39.008 --> 14:41.358
that you were gonna leave
your door unlocked for Vince?

14:51.586 --> 14:51.803
.

14:51.847 --> 14:54.154
- So Audrey told a priest
in confession

14:54.197 --> 14:56.547
that she was going to leave
her door unlocked?

14:56.591 --> 14:58.941
I take it that we don't know
which priest that was?

14:58.985 --> 15:00.247
- No.

15:00.290 --> 15:01.726
But at the parish
that Saturday,

15:01.770 --> 15:03.598
it would have been
one of two:

15:03.641 --> 15:06.383
Father John Regis--
he's the church pastor--

15:06.427 --> 15:09.821
or Father Ryan Duffy--
he's the associate pastor.

15:09.865 --> 15:12.650
- We don't really think
it was a priest, do we?

15:12.694 --> 15:14.391
I mean, maybe somebody
overheard.

15:14.435 --> 15:16.263
- Well, that's why priests
speak softly.

15:16.306 --> 15:18.526
Full disclosure, um,
Father Duffy and I

15:18.569 --> 15:20.180
have been friends
since middle school.

15:20.223 --> 15:22.704
Liv, I really don't see this.

15:22.747 --> 15:25.315
- Wouldn't be the first time
we perp-walked a priest.

15:25.359 --> 15:26.534
- Okay, we're all aware, Fin.

15:26.577 --> 15:28.753
Uh, but this would be
a pretty big jump.

15:28.797 --> 15:31.408
CSU found no prints,
semen, touch DNA,

15:31.452 --> 15:33.149
nothing from the rape kit.

15:33.193 --> 15:35.151
- Is it possible that--

15:35.195 --> 15:37.806
that Father Regis
or Father Duffy

15:37.849 --> 15:41.288
mentioned the affair
or, you know, the unlocked door

15:41.331 --> 15:43.986
to--to somebody else?
Like, in passing?

15:44.030 --> 15:45.422
- You mean gossip?
No.

15:45.466 --> 15:47.163
That would be in violation
of the confessional seal.

15:47.207 --> 15:48.425
- Somebody knew

15:48.469 --> 15:49.905
that the door
would be unlocked, Carisi.

15:49.949 --> 15:53.300
I--I know that this is
an uncomfortable conversation,

15:53.343 --> 15:58.392
but--but somebody has to ask.

15:58.435 --> 16:01.221
- This is about Audrey O'Neill,
isn't it?

16:01.264 --> 16:02.700
Did you speak to her?
- Yeah.

16:02.744 --> 16:04.398
Yeah I did.

16:04.441 --> 16:06.269
Turns out she was raped.

16:06.313 --> 16:08.706
- Oh, that poor woman.

16:08.750 --> 16:10.534
Hope you were able to help her.

16:10.578 --> 16:12.710
- We're investigating.

16:12.754 --> 16:15.583
So far, our only lead
leads us here.

16:15.626 --> 16:17.280
- I'm not sure I understand.

16:17.324 --> 16:18.542
- The rapist knew

16:18.586 --> 16:20.501
Audrey was gonna leave
her door unlocked

16:20.544 --> 16:22.329
the night of the assault.
- I see.

16:22.372 --> 16:23.895
- And as far as we can tell,

16:23.939 --> 16:26.855
she didn't tell anyone else
she was gonna do that

16:26.898 --> 16:29.684
except for a priest.

16:29.727 --> 16:31.033
- I've already told you,
I--

16:31.077 --> 16:33.905
- We're not asking
if you took her confession.

16:33.949 --> 16:36.212
Is there any chance

16:36.256 --> 16:37.561
that maybe somebody
overheard you

16:37.605 --> 16:39.215
or you inadvertently shared
that information?

16:39.259 --> 16:41.348
- Dominick...

16:41.391 --> 16:42.914
even when we played
little league together,

16:42.958 --> 16:44.090
remember?

16:44.133 --> 16:45.613
I'd never share
our signs with anyone.

16:45.656 --> 16:46.962
- This is not a game, Father.

16:47.006 --> 16:49.182
- Let alone
confessional secrets.

16:49.225 --> 16:53.142
I take this news
very seriously.

16:53.186 --> 16:56.580
Look, whatever I can do
to help,

16:56.624 --> 16:58.930
without breaking my vows.

16:58.974 --> 17:00.149
- Okay, Father.

17:00.193 --> 17:02.847
Where were you Friday night
around 9:30?

17:02.891 --> 17:05.807
[tense music]

17:05.850 --> 17:08.070
♪

17:08.114 --> 17:10.855
- In my bedroom, reading.

17:10.899 --> 17:16.122
- Can someone verify that?
- No, I was alone, door closed.

17:16.165 --> 17:17.819
- Where was Father Regis?

17:17.862 --> 17:22.258
♪

17:22.302 --> 17:24.434
- Well, you'd have to ask him.

17:24.478 --> 17:26.697
- Yes, I heard
about Mrs. O'Neill.

17:26.741 --> 17:28.960
This city's getting worse.

17:29.004 --> 17:30.266
I'm praying for her.

17:30.310 --> 17:33.052
- Well, um, we need
more than that, Father.

17:33.095 --> 17:34.444
- How can I help?

17:34.488 --> 17:35.619
- We need to find out

17:35.663 --> 17:37.273
if something
Audrey said in confession

17:37.317 --> 17:39.319
might have been mentioned
to someone else.

17:39.362 --> 17:40.494
- By the priest?
No, that's--

17:40.537 --> 17:41.799
that's not possible.

17:41.843 --> 17:44.106
If you read your catechism,
Sergeant,

17:44.150 --> 17:46.195
you'd know
that no priest worth his faith

17:46.239 --> 17:48.545
would ever repeat anything
outside of the confessional.

17:48.589 --> 17:50.330
- We didn't mean intentionally.

17:50.373 --> 17:52.897
We're all human.
Sometimes things slip.

17:52.941 --> 17:56.336
- They do,
but not something like that.

17:56.379 --> 17:58.381
I will reach out
to Mrs. O'Neill

17:58.425 --> 18:00.644
and let her know
I'm here for her

18:00.688 --> 18:02.603
if she needs counseling.

18:02.646 --> 18:05.171
- Thank you, Father.
- Thank you.

18:05.214 --> 18:07.521
- One more thing, Father.

18:07.564 --> 18:10.263
Where were you at 9:30,
Friday night?

18:10.306 --> 18:11.829
- Me?

18:11.873 --> 18:13.962
I was in my room,
writing my Sunday homily.

18:14.005 --> 18:16.573
- Alone?
- I'm a priest, detective,

18:16.617 --> 18:18.271
not a rabbi or a minister.

18:18.314 --> 18:21.491
Yes, we are alone in our rooms.

18:21.535 --> 18:23.493
I wish you luck
finding this man.

18:23.537 --> 18:27.715
Meantime, as I said,
I will be praying for her.

18:29.891 --> 18:31.806
- Okay, so either Father Duffy
or Father Regis

18:31.849 --> 18:33.329
could have taken
her confession.

18:33.373 --> 18:35.418
- But neither one
can talk about it

18:35.462 --> 18:37.159
because
of the confessional seal.

18:37.203 --> 18:38.595
- Lucky for one of them.

18:38.639 --> 18:40.597
- Do either one of them
have a good alibi?

18:40.641 --> 18:42.033
- Not really.

18:42.077 --> 18:43.513
But I checked with TARU,
and neither of their phones

18:43.557 --> 18:44.949
left the rectory that night.

18:44.993 --> 18:46.516
- That just means that
the rapist was smart enough

18:46.560 --> 18:48.388
to leave the phone at home.

18:48.431 --> 18:51.869
I hate to point to a priest,
but...

18:51.913 --> 18:53.175
we don't have another suspect.

18:53.219 --> 18:58.485
- It's not like either one's
gonna confess.

18:58.528 --> 19:01.183
- Look, guys,
this may be a long shot,

19:01.227 --> 19:05.622
but maybe--maybe we try
to catfish the priest.

19:05.666 --> 19:10.410
We send in a UC
to confess to both priests

19:10.453 --> 19:13.413
about being alone,
waiting for a lover...

19:13.456 --> 19:17.199
- And see if one of them
takes the bait.

19:17.243 --> 19:19.288
Got you, captain.
We're on it.

19:19.332 --> 19:22.248
[suspenseful music]

19:22.291 --> 19:28.602
♪

19:28.645 --> 19:30.734
- Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

19:30.778 --> 19:33.737
It has been three months
since my last confession.

19:33.781 --> 19:37.088
In that time, I have been
cheating on my husband.

19:37.132 --> 19:40.004
He's a kind man,
but I've met someone,

19:40.048 --> 19:43.486
and I've been unable to control
my urges to be with him.

19:43.530 --> 19:46.576
♪

19:46.620 --> 19:50.232
I told my lover
to meet me again tonight.

19:50.276 --> 19:53.888
I work at a gallery downtown
called Art Thou Mad.

19:53.931 --> 19:55.672
There's a back room
where we could be

19:55.716 --> 19:58.153
alone together after closing.

19:58.197 --> 20:01.112
I gave him the security code
to the entrance.

20:01.156 --> 20:03.202
Forgive me,
but I changed the code

20:03.245 --> 20:06.379
to the day of Saint Dwynwyn.

20:06.422 --> 20:08.946
I have prayed for the strength
to remain faithful,

20:08.990 --> 20:12.602
but I know I won't
be able to tonight.

20:12.646 --> 20:15.039
- Saint who?
- Dwynwyn.

20:15.083 --> 20:17.433
The patron saint of lovers,
right?

20:17.477 --> 20:19.740
- I figured both priests
would know it.

20:19.783 --> 20:22.612
I made
the same confession twice.

20:22.656 --> 20:26.660
Now what?
- We wait for the sinner.

20:35.843 --> 20:38.280
- I got incoming.
Male, about six foot.

20:38.324 --> 20:39.629
No visuals on his face,

20:39.673 --> 20:40.978
but it looks
like he's punching in the code.

20:41.022 --> 20:42.153
[lock buzzes]

20:42.197 --> 20:44.286
- Copy that.
Standing by.

20:44.330 --> 20:47.289
[tense music]

20:47.333 --> 20:54.253
♪

20:59.867 --> 21:01.651
- NYPD.
- Hands where we can see them.

21:01.695 --> 21:05.307
- Don't shoot, don't shoot!

21:05.351 --> 21:06.656
- Father Duffy.

21:06.700 --> 21:08.397
- What--there--
this isn't how it looks.

21:08.441 --> 21:09.833
- It looks bad, Father.

21:09.877 --> 21:11.661
- I never would have hurt you.

21:11.705 --> 21:14.708
- Put your hands
behind your back.

21:14.751 --> 21:16.318
It's ring around
the collar time.

21:16.362 --> 21:18.494
- [sighs]

21:18.538 --> 21:21.889
Tell Dominick I'm sorry.

21:27.242 --> 21:27.373
.

21:27.416 --> 21:28.852
- I used to tell myself

21:28.896 --> 21:31.159
that unlike both my parents,

21:31.202 --> 21:33.248
I had things under control.

21:33.292 --> 21:35.859
That I--I was drinking
just up to the point,

21:35.903 --> 21:39.385
but not past the point,
where I was drinking so much

21:39.428 --> 21:41.952
that, God forbid,
I'd have to quit.

21:41.996 --> 21:43.650
[chuckling]

21:43.693 --> 21:45.216
I was not only ignoring
the damage

21:45.260 --> 21:47.915
I was doing to myself,

21:47.958 --> 21:52.223
but to my friends, family...

21:53.616 --> 21:54.922
Others.

21:54.965 --> 21:57.881
[quiet dramatic music]

21:57.925 --> 22:01.711
♪

22:01.755 --> 22:06.499
And by others, I mean women.

22:06.542 --> 22:12.853
The list of women I hurt
trying to fill this...

22:12.896 --> 22:18.162
bottomless hole mortifies me.

22:21.252 --> 22:24.821
Including
my first real girlfriend.

22:30.740 --> 22:33.613
And she was just a girl.

22:37.268 --> 22:41.708
I met her
when I was 21 years old.

22:41.751 --> 22:46.103
I was just about
to get kicked out of college.

22:46.147 --> 22:48.105
Thank you for coming
to the meeting.

22:48.149 --> 22:49.237
I know how busy you are.

22:49.280 --> 22:50.673
- I'm glad that I came.

22:50.717 --> 22:54.851
I could see you've done
a lot of work on yourself.

22:54.895 --> 22:57.201
- Mm.
Still needs doing.

22:57.245 --> 22:59.116
[chuckles]

22:59.160 --> 23:01.249
First I dried out,
went back to therapy,

23:01.292 --> 23:03.077
found these meetings.

23:03.120 --> 23:04.513
You've already heard
most of my spiel,

23:04.557 --> 23:09.257
but there is something
that I need for you to know.

23:09.300 --> 23:11.955
However inappropriate it was--

23:11.999 --> 23:13.522
and God knows you were right,

23:13.566 --> 23:15.742
the age difference,
the power imbalance--

23:15.785 --> 23:22.313
but, Olivia, I really was
in love with you.

23:25.316 --> 23:27.623
- I was in love
with you, too, Burton.

23:31.018 --> 23:32.411
But that--
- I know.

23:32.454 --> 23:34.717
Doesn't make anything right.
I know, I know.

23:34.761 --> 23:36.327
[phone buzzes]

23:37.111 --> 23:39.069
- Sorry.

23:39.113 --> 23:41.463
I'm--I'm sorry.
I have to go.

23:41.507 --> 23:46.425
My squad just arrested a man
for rape.

23:47.556 --> 23:50.211
- Hey.
- Detective Ruz did great.

23:50.254 --> 23:52.039
Her confession
about being alone,

23:52.082 --> 23:53.301
waiting on a lover--

23:53.344 --> 23:54.520
that was all Duffy needed
to hear.

23:54.563 --> 23:56.173
- Okay, did Father Duffy
say anything?

23:56.217 --> 23:57.653
- He said it wasn't
what it looked like.

23:57.697 --> 23:59.786
- Well, maybe it wasn't.
Maybe we should hear his side.

23:59.829 --> 24:02.005
- His side?
He showed up on time.

24:02.049 --> 24:03.616
He was dressed in black.

24:03.659 --> 24:06.314
He used the security code.
He let himself in.

24:06.357 --> 24:07.620
This is the same MO as Audrey.

24:07.663 --> 24:09.535
- Okay, where is
Father Duffy now?

24:09.578 --> 24:11.232
- Dominick, I wish
I could tell you

24:11.275 --> 24:12.712
why I was there tonight,
but I can't.

24:12.755 --> 24:14.540
- I'm not asking what you heard
in the confessional,

24:14.583 --> 24:16.498
because I know what you heard.
- Yeah, I realize that now.

24:16.542 --> 24:18.195
You sent in a detective
to take advantage

24:18.239 --> 24:19.414
of the confessional booth?

24:19.458 --> 24:20.459
- You want to know
who took advantage

24:20.502 --> 24:21.764
of the confessional booth?

24:21.808 --> 24:23.505
The priest that raped
Audrey O'Neill.

24:23.549 --> 24:24.724
- I didn't assault
Audrey O'Neill.

24:24.767 --> 24:26.073
And I wasn't
at that art gallery

24:26.116 --> 24:27.204
to assault anyone tonight.

24:27.248 --> 24:28.510
- Then why were you there,
Ryan?

24:28.554 --> 24:31.382
- I've done nothing wrong.

24:31.426 --> 24:33.472
- Well, then you better
get a lawyer.

24:33.515 --> 24:35.735
- The diocese is sending one.

24:35.778 --> 24:38.651
[tense music]

24:38.694 --> 24:43.351
But I--I can't tell him
why I was there either.

24:43.394 --> 24:45.527
- Ryan, you are swimming
in some dangerous,

24:45.571 --> 24:48.530
unholy waters right now.

24:48.574 --> 24:50.532
Now, we've been friends
for a long time.

24:50.576 --> 24:54.667
I need you to listen to me.
- I need for you to believe me.

24:54.710 --> 25:00.237
- I want to.
But I don't know how.

25:00.281 --> 25:02.152
- Then pray for me.

25:02.196 --> 25:06.548
- Counselor Carisi,
Father Duffy's lawyer's here,

25:06.592 --> 25:09.420
and you shouldn't be.

25:12.162 --> 25:14.817
Counselor...

25:14.861 --> 25:17.820
[somber music]

25:17.864 --> 25:25.045
♪

25:25.436 --> 25:28.265
- You have my client
on trespassing at best.

25:28.309 --> 25:30.050
But burglary
and attempted rape?

25:30.093 --> 25:32.748
Father Duffy had no intention
to assault your detective.

25:32.792 --> 25:34.402
- Uh-huh.

25:34.445 --> 25:36.230
So why'd you break
into the gallery, Father?

25:36.273 --> 25:39.320
You an art thief?
- Easy, Fin.

25:39.363 --> 25:42.149
Just tell us
why you were there, Father.

25:42.192 --> 25:45.979
Help yourself.
- I was concerned.

25:46.022 --> 25:47.589
- Concerned about what?

25:47.633 --> 25:50.287
- I wanted to make sure
the woman there was safe.

25:50.331 --> 25:52.942
- How'd you even know
she was there?

25:52.986 --> 25:54.814
- [sighs]
I can't answer that either.

25:54.857 --> 25:57.251
- That line's getting old
real fast, man.

25:57.294 --> 25:58.644
- There are edicts
that Father Duffy

25:58.687 --> 26:00.428
is bound to oblige
under canon law.

26:00.471 --> 26:01.690
He violates any one of those,

26:01.734 --> 26:03.997
he faces excommunication
from the Church.

26:04.040 --> 26:06.086
- And if he doesn't come
with a better story real soon,

26:06.129 --> 26:08.349
he's gonna be indicted,
convicted, and sentenced.

26:08.392 --> 26:09.655
That's his choice.

26:09.698 --> 26:11.221
- Well, I'd--
I have to choose prison then.

26:11.265 --> 26:12.701
- Well, suit yourself.

26:12.745 --> 26:13.833
If you live long enough
to get out,

26:13.876 --> 26:15.574
you'll be an ex-priest
and an ex-con.

26:15.617 --> 26:17.706
- And this colloquy is over.

26:20.927 --> 26:22.493
- I've known him
since we were kids, Liv.

26:22.537 --> 26:24.495
He's--he's no rapist.

26:24.539 --> 26:26.933
- We've all been blind-sided,
Carisi, right?

26:26.976 --> 26:30.893
Sometimes people just aren't
who we--we thought they were

26:30.937 --> 26:33.461
or hoped they were.
- Still...

26:33.504 --> 26:34.984
- Why else was he there?

26:35.028 --> 26:37.465
- There's only
one other possibility.

26:37.508 --> 26:39.946
That he knows
who Audrey's rapist is,

26:39.989 --> 26:42.644
and--and he thought
he was gonna strike again.

26:42.688 --> 26:44.777
- Why wouldn't
he just tell us that?

26:47.083 --> 26:49.999
[somber music]

26:50.043 --> 26:51.392
♪

26:51.435 --> 26:54.351
- Because the rapist
confessed to him.

27:02.142 --> 27:02.359
.

27:02.403 --> 27:04.187
- Father Duffy got arraigned.

27:04.231 --> 27:05.624
That must have been tough
on Carisi.

27:05.667 --> 27:07.190
- Just
on the trespassing charge.

27:07.234 --> 27:09.149
Carisi'll have
to recuse himself

27:09.192 --> 27:11.368
if this goes to a rape trial.
- But it won't.

27:11.412 --> 27:14.328
Carisi thinks the actual rapist
confessed to Father Duffy.

27:14.371 --> 27:16.199
- Ruz goes to confession.

27:16.243 --> 27:18.985
She tells two priests
she'll be alone that night.

27:19.028 --> 27:22.379
One priest shows up.
What am I missing?

27:22.423 --> 27:26.688
- Maybe the other priest,
Father Regis.

27:26.732 --> 27:29.735
Priests go to confession too.
- Right.

27:29.778 --> 27:32.738
So Father Regis confesses
to Father Duffy

27:32.781 --> 27:34.522
that he had the urge
to rape again.

27:34.565 --> 27:38.526
- And Father Duffy shows up
at the gallery to intercede.

27:38.569 --> 27:40.180
If Father Regis is the rapist,

27:40.223 --> 27:42.182
then he has
a particular pattern.

27:42.225 --> 27:44.010
How long has he been
at the parish?

27:44.053 --> 27:45.359
- Three years.
But I checked

27:45.402 --> 27:47.013
with the local precinct,
and there's no open rapes

27:47.056 --> 27:49.189
on any married, Catholic women
during the timeframe.

27:49.232 --> 27:51.060
- Priests do get transferred.

27:51.104 --> 27:53.149
So find out where he was before

27:53.193 --> 27:55.238
and see if there are
any unsolved rapes

27:55.282 --> 27:59.112
at that parish.
- Copy that.

28:01.244 --> 28:03.638
